Mark a dimple in the center of the body cap with the center punch tool. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2f/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2f/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Using a nail or similar tool is also effective. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ee/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ee/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Using a soda can with the top and bottom cut off, cut a 3/4" (1.9 cm) square to 1" (2.5cm) square piece. The size does not need to be exact nor exactly square, however the size must be small enough to fit flush inside the body cap yet large enough to hold while sanding. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Round the corners of the square piece for safety. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take a sturdy sharp needle, and slowly use a twisting motion with gentle pressure, to make a dimple in the center of the aluminum. Go slowly and steadily so as not to create a hole that is too large. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/87\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/87\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

The dimple should be just visible on the underside of the aluminum piece. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/18\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/18\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Do not push the needle all the way through; there shouldn't be a visible hole at this point, only a dimple.

Take a photo. Look at the histogram. If the graph indicates that the image is over-exposed (the histogram will show data bunched to the extreme right) or under-exposed (histogram data is bunched to the left), adjust the shutter speed to compensate. Once the exposure is set you can use this exposure while shooting in similar light conditions. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/3a\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/3a\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Depending on how bright the scene is your exposure time may vary from several seconds to just under a second. The yellow flower photo shown here was exposed for 1/2 a second at ISO 400 in full sun. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/af\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/af\/Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Make-a-Pinhole-Lens-for-Your-SLR-Camera-Step-18Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

The sun through the leaves photo was exposed for 1/15 of a second at ISO 400. If your scene lighting changes, recheck the histogram and adjust shutter speed to compensate.
